                        <h1>Five Ways to Keep Your Teeth Clean After Whitening</h1>
                        <p>So you&rsquo;ve had your teeth whitened, and they&rsquo;re looking amazing! Congratulations! But how do you keep them that way?</p>
                        <p>The short answer is: you can&rsquo;t. Over time, the same elements that went into discoloring them in the first place (diet, drinks, smoking, etc.) will gradually remove the sparkling white, and you&rsquo;ll have to have your teeth whitened all over again. However, the good news is that there are ways and means of prolonging that from happening anytime soon.</p>
